Description: Multi-WAN uplink manager with IPv4 failover and IPv6 multi-homing
 uplinkmgr configures a Linux router to handle multiple internet (WAN)
 uplinks with automatic failover for IPv4 and multi-homing for IPv6.
 .
 It provides metric-ordered IPv4 default routes (highest-priority live
 uplink wins), SLAAC-based IPv6 multi-homing via macvlan interfaces and
 per-uplink prefix delegation, and graceful degradation through radvd
 AdvDefaultPreference signalling when an uplink fails.
 .
 Components: uplinkmgr-setup (generates static config), a dhcpcd exit
 hook (maintains per-uplink routing tables), and the uplinkmgr daemon
 (monitors uplinks and manages radvd lifecycle).
